  "raw_text": "\n\n# **I AM THE CHANGE**\n\n## Scholarship Program \u2014 Home Visit Questionnaire\n\nTeam Everest | Confidential\n\nVolunteer Name:\n\nGeetha Hande\n\nCo-Volunteer Name:\n\nWent with family\n\nDate of Visit:\n\n4<sup>th</sup> Jul 2026\n\n## **Section 1 \u2014 Student Profile**\n\n### **1.1. Application ID**\n\nEnter Application ID\n\nTEMP - 2026 - 8437\n\n### **1.2. Student Full Name**\n\nEnter full name\n\nSadhana S\n\n### **1.3. Gender**\n\n\u2610 Male\u2612 Female\u2610 Others\n\n## **Section 2 \u2014 Family Background**\n\n### **2.1. Family Status**\n\n\u2612 Single Parent\u2610 Parentless\u2610 Having both parents\n\n### **2.2. Relationship Details (if applicable)**\n\n| Year of Death / Separation | Reason for Death / Separation   |\n|----------------------------|---------------------------------|\n| Mother's death -<br>2021   | Aggravated Asthama during Covid |\n\n\n\n### 2.3. Is Father/ Mother photograph kept at home?\n\n\u2612 Yes \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 No\n\n### 2.4. Government ID Verified (Ration Card / Aadhaar / Driving Licence / Voter ID)\n\n\u2612 Aadhaar Card \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Ration Card \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Driving Licence \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Voter ID\n\n\u2610 Other: \\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n### 2.5. Family Members\n\n| Name       | Age | Education                  | Occupation             | Annual Income |\n|------------|-----|----------------------------|------------------------|---------------|\n| Hemalatha  | 64  | 9 <sup>th</sup> std        | \u2014                      |               |\n| Sudharshan | 45  | 10 <sup>th</sup> std       | Swiggy delivery person | ~ 1,80,000    |\n| Mithun     | 14  | 10 <sup>th</sup> std study | Student                | \u2014             |\n| Sadharan   | 17  | 1 <sup>st</sup> year B.com | Student                |               |\n\n## Section 3 \u2014 Housing Condition\n\n### 3.1. House Ownership\n\n\u2610 Own \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Rented\n\n#### 3.1.1 If rented, what is the rent amount?\n\nRent amount\n\nRs. 5,000/-\n\n### 3.2. Type of Home\n\n\u2610 Individual \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Private Apartment \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Housing Board \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Line House \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610\n\nOthers: \\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n\n\n## 3.3. Type of Ceiling\n\n- \u2610 Roof (Kurai) \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Tiled \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Asbestos / Sheet \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Concrete\n\n### 3.4. Number of Bedrooms\n\nEnter number\n\n1\n\n### 3.4.1. Type of Bedroom\n\n- \u2612 Separate Bedroom \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 No Separate Bedroom\n\n### 3.5. Bathroom\n\n- \u2612 Separate \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Common for Apartment\n\n### 3.6. Kitchen Type\n\n- \u2612 Separate Kitchen <sup>(Small)</sup> \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Hall with Kitchen\n\n## Section 4 \u2014 Financial Background\n\n### 4.1. Assets at Home (tick all that apply)\n\n- \u2612 Washing Machine \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Fridge \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 AC \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 LED TV \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Two-Wheeler \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Car\n- \u2612 Smartphone \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Separate Wi-Fi \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Others: \\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n### 4.2. Amount of Last Electricity Bill\n\nAmount in \u20b9\n\nRs. 1800 + (For 2 months)\n\n### 4.3. Do you own any other assets/properties in the name of grandparents, parents, or student?\n\n- \u2610 Yes \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 No\n\n\n\n4.3.1 If yes, list their properties:\n\n| Property Description | Owner Name | Approximate Value |\n|----------------------|------------|-------------------|\n|                      |            |                   |\n|                      |            |                   |\n\n4.4. Apart from your job, is there any other source of income?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 No\n\n4.4.1 If yes, list other sources of income:\n\n| Source of Income | Amount |\n|------------------|--------|\n|                  |        |\n|                  |        |\n\n4.5. Income Type\n\n\u2610 Monthly \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Daily \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 Weekly \u00a0\u00a0 \u2610 Ad-Hoc\n\n4.6. Do you have any loans?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u00a0\u00a0 \u2612 No\n\n4.6.1 If yes, share Loan Purpose, Amount Taken, and Pending Loan Amount:\n\n| Sr. No. | Loan Purpose | Loan Amount Taken | Pending Loan Amount |\n|---------|--------------|-------------------|---------------------|\n|         |              |                   |                     |\n|         |              |                   |                     |\n|         |              |                   |                     |\n\n\n\n4.7. If you choose any college, how much is the college fee?\n\nAmount in \u20b9\n\nEthiraj College (Rs. 1,05,000)\n\n4.8. If the college fee is higher, how will you manage it?\n\nSold the vehicle for first sem fees (Rs. 51,000)\n\n4.9. If you do not receive this scholarship, how will you pay the fees?\n\nNo plan, they are just hoping for some avenues.\n\n# Section 5 \u2014 Health Information\n\n5.1. Does the student have any health issues?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u2612 No\n\n5.2. If yes, list the health issues:\n\nDescribe health issues\n\n# Section 6 \u2014 Student Commitment\n\n6.1. Will you study college for three years without any obstacle?\n\nSeems to be committed, Yes. Planning to take up CA  \nteaching side by side (through online recorded sessions)\n\n6.2. If we have a training program within 15 km from your home, can you come?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u2610 No \u2612 Maybe\n\nFather works on all 6 days + has to cope up with ongoing  \nStudies Will try to attend\n\n\n\n6.3. Are you ready to send your son/daughter to weekly skill development classes on Sundays (16 classes a year)?\n\n\u2610 Yes \u2610 No [may be]\n\n# Section 7 \u2014 Scholarship Information\n\n7.1. Has the student received or applied for any other scholarships for their UG degree?\n\nNothing so far\n\n# Section 8 \u2014 Volunteer Observation\n\n8.1. What is your opinion about the student, their family members, and their living condition?\n\nStudent is very bright and has clear focus on what she wants to do.  \nFamily members (Grandmother, father & 